e until order is restored, before hundreds of fans then invade the pitch on the final whistle. The incident will be investigated by the [[Football Association]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Jason |last=Burt |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/aston-villa/11457075/Aston-Villa-pitch-invasion-to-spark-Football-Association-investigation.html |title=Aston Villa pitch invasion to spark Football Association investigation |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=7 March 2015 |accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31669806 |work=BBC Sport |title=Aston Villa 2-0 West Bromwich Albion |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=7 March 2015 |accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref>\n*8 March \u2013 Ed Miliband says that a future Labour government would introduce legislation to make televised debates a permanent feature of future general election campaigns, meaning politicians could not attempt to prevent them from taking place out of self-interest.<ref>{{cite news|first=Toby |last=Helm |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/mar/07/ed-miliband-leaders-tv-debates-guarantee-law |title=Ed Miliband: I will pass new law to guarantee TV election debates|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|newspaper=The Observer|date=8 March 2015|accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref>\n*9 March\n**The U.K. Government finally pays off War Loan bonds, originally introduced to consolidate debt incurred in fighting [[World War I]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Better late than never! UK finally repays its First World War debts|url=https://www.rt.com/uk/238969-ww1-debt-uk-repaid/|work=RT|accessdate=6 October 2018|date=9 March 2015}}</ref>\n**Thendara Satisfaction, an [[Irish setter]] who competed at this year's [[Crufts]], dies after being supposedly poisoned at the [[Birmingham]] show.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-31792152|work=[[BBC News]]|title='No doubt' Crufts dog Jagger was poisoned, says owner|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=9 March 2015|accessdate=9 March 2015}}</ref> Organisers of the event say sabotage will not be tolerated, after rumours that various other dogs were also poisoned this year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-31807943|work=[[BBC News]]|title='No tolerance' vow after Crufts dog Jagger dies|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=9 March 2015|accessdate=9 March 2015}}</ref>\n*10 March\n**[[Queen Elizabeth II]] names the new luxury cruise ship ''[[MV Britannia (2015)|Britannia]]'', the largest ever cruise ship designed for the British holiday market.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-hampshire-31802613 |work=[[BBC News]] |title=Cruise ship Britannia: Queen names P&O luxury vessel |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=10 March 2015 |accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n**TV presenter [[Jeremy Clarkson]] is suspended from ''[[Top Gear (2002 TV series)|Top Gear]]'', one of the BBC's most popular and profitable shows, after a \"fracas\" with a producer. The remainder of the series will be scrapped, the BBC says.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://m.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31824040 |title=Jeremy Clarkson, Top Gear host, suspended by BBC after 'fracas' |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=10 March 2015 |accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://m.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31828184 |title=Jeremy Clarkson 'punch': Top Gear episodes to be dropped |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=11 March 2015 |accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref>\n*11 March \u2013 the government announces the first NHS patients to be diagnosed through [[genome sequencing]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/first-patients-diagnosed-through-genome-sequencing |title=First patients diagnosed through genome sequencing |publisher=Department of Health|date=11 March 2015 |accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref>\n*13 March \u2013 following his guilty verdict on 13 February, former TV weather presenter Fred Talbot is