nder the name of the [[Borders Railway]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-south-scotland-34108746|title=Borders-to-Edinburgh railway opens as longest UK line in century|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=6 September 2015|accessdate=6 September 2015}}</ref>\n**Homeowners in [[Lancashire]] are told that their water supplies are safe and back to normal after a [[cryptosporidium|microbial parasite]] contaminated [[drinking water]] for more than three weeks.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-lancashire-34169201|title=Lancashire water supplies declared safe|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=6 September 2015|accessdate=6 September 2015}}</ref>\n**The [[Lieutenant Governor of Guernsey]], [[Peter Walker (RAF officer)|Peter Walker]], dies in office.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-guernsey-34167596|title=Guernsey Lieutenant-Governor, Air Marshal Peter Walker dies|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=6 September 2015|accessdate=8 September 2015}}</ref>\n*7 September \u2013 two British [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]] [[jihadists]], who were planning \"barbaric\" attacks on British soil, are confirmed dead after the first targeted UK drone attack on a British citizen last month.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34178998|title=Islamic State conflict: Two Britons killed in RAF Syria strike|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=7 September 2015|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n*9 September \u2013 [[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II]] surpasses her great-great-grandmother [[Queen Victoria]] as [[List of monarchs in Britain by length of reign|Britain's longest-reigning monarch]],<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-13363504 \"Queen Elizabeth II marks another milestone\"]. BBC. 12 May 2011. Retrieved 12 December 2014.</ref> as she declares the [[Borders Railway]] officially open.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-south-scotland-34177585|title=Queen officially opens Borders-to-Edinburgh railway|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=9 September 2015|accessdate=9 September 2015}}</ref>\n*11 September \u2013 MPs reject plans for a [[right to die]] in England and Wales in their first vote on the issue in almost twenty years.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-34208624|title=Assisted Dying Bill: MPs reject 'right to die' law|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=11 September 2015|accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref>\n*12 September \u2013 [[Jeremy Corbyn]] is elected as the new leader of the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34223157|title=Jeremy Corbyn wins Labour leadership contest|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=12 September 2015|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref> with [[Tom Watson (Labour politician)|Tom Watson]] as deputy leader.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34232388|title=Tom Watson elected deputy leader of the Labour Party|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=12 September 2015|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n*15 September \u2013 a flypast takes place at [[Goodwood, West Sussex|Goodwood]] in West Sussex to mark the seventy-fifth anniversary of the [[Battle of Britain]]. A service to mark the occasion is also held at [[St Paul's Cathedral]] in London, attended by David Cameron, Jeremy Corbyn, and the visiting [[Andrzej Duda|President of Poland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34250794|title=Battle of Britain; Historic flypast for 75th anniversary|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=15 September 2015|accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref>\n*22 September \u2013 Chancellor [[George Osborne]] says during a visit to China that the country \"must be the United Kingdom's number two export market\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34325714|title='China must be our number two export market'|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=22 September 2015|accessdate=22 September 2015}}</ref>\n*26 September \u2013 a fire damages the United Kingdom's largest mosque, the [[Baitul Futuh Mosque]] in Mo