515763|title=Hate crimes increase by 18% in England and Wales|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=13 October 2015|accessdate=13 October 2015}}</ref>\n*15 October \u2013 the [[Stirling Prize]], the United Kingdom's top architectural award, is given to [[Burntwood School]] in [[Wandsworth]], London.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-34537420|title=Riba Stirling Prize: Burntwood School wins award|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=15 October 2015|accessdate=15 October 2015}}</ref>\n*16 October \u2013 Scottish National Party leader [[Nicola Sturgeon]] announces at the annual SNP conference, that party membership now stands at 114,221 members.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-34553158|title=SNP Conference 2015: Who are the party's new members?|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=16 October 2015|accessdate=23 October 2015}}</ref>\n*19 October \u2013 Chinese President [[Xi Jinping]] arrives at [[Heathrow Airport]] for his [[2015 Xi Jinping visit to the United Kingdom|first state visit]] to the UK.<ref>{{cite news|title=Chinese President Xi Jinping arrives in UK|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-34571910|website=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=19 October 2015}}</ref>\n*20 October \u2013 [[Michael Meacher]], the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] MP for [[Oldham West and Royton (UK Parliament constituency)|Oldham West and Royton]], dies in office.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34592381|title=Labour MP Michael Meacher dies|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=21 October 2015|accessdate=21 October 2015}}</ref>\n*22 October \u2013 the voting rights of Scottish MPs are to be restricted, after the Conservative Government wins a vote on its controversial '[[West Lothian question|English votes for English laws]]\u2019 (EVEL) plans.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/13888756.Voting_rights_of_Scottish_MPs_to_be_restricted_after_Government_wins_Evel_vote/|title=Voting rights of Scottish MPs to be restricted after Government wins Evel vote|publisher=The Herald|date=22 October 2015|accessdate=23 October 2015}}</ref>\n*23 October \u2013 a \"significant and sustained\" [[cyberattack]] is made on the website of telecoms firm [[TalkTalk Group|TalkTalk]], with personal and banking details of up to 4,000,000 customers being accessed and the firm's CEO receiving a ransom email purported to be from the hackers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34615226 |title=TalkTalk cyber-attack: Boss 'receives ransom email' |publisher=[[BBC]]|date=23 October 2015|accessdate=23 October 2015}}</ref>\n*25 October\n**The [[Royal Mint]] releases a special \u00a35 coin to commemorate the six-hundredth anniversary of the [[Battle of Agincourt]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-east-wales-34628126|title=Royal Mint releases coin to mark Battle of Agincourt anniversary|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=25 October 2015|accessdate=26 October 2015}}</ref>\n**Five people, all confirmed to be Britons, are drowned after the whale-watching boat ''Leviathan II'' sinks off [[Tofino]] in [[British Columbia]], Canada.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1576411/whale-watching-boat-tragedy-kills-five-britons|title=Whale-watching boat tragedy kills five Britons|publisher=Sky News|date=26 October 2015|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref>\n*26 October\n**[[Rachel Treweek]], [[Bishop of Gloucester]], becomes the first woman to take her seat as a bishop in the [[House of Lords (United Kingdom)|House of Lords]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34634819 |title=Gloucester bishop Rachel Treweek to take seat in Lords |work=[[BBC News]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=26 October 2015 |accessdate=26 October 2015}}</ref>\n**The government suffers a major defeat in the House of Lords, after its plans to cut [[Tax credit#United Kingdom|tax credits]] are rejected by peers, who vote to delay the measures and compensate those affected in full.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34631156 |title=Tax credits: Lords vote to delay controversial cuts |publisher=[[BBC]]|date=26 October 2015|accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref>\n*29 October\n**A sixteen-year-old youth is detained by police, after a fellow pupil is stabbed to death at [[Cults Academy]] school in [[Aberdeen]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-north-east-orkney-shetland-34660140|title=Pupil dies after school stabbing at Cults Academy near Aberdeen|work=[[BBC News]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=29 October 2015 |accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref>\n**It is projected that the UK population will increase beyond 70,000,000 by [[2027]], mainly due to an ageing population and net migration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34666382|title=UK population 'to top 70 million in 12 years'|work=[[BBC News]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=29 October 2015 |accessdate=30 October 2015}}</ref>\n*30 October \u2013 [[Shaker Aamer]], the last British resident to be held in [[Guantanamo Bay detention camp|Guantanamo Bay]], lands in the UK, having been detained for thirteen years.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34675324|title=Shaker Aamer: Last UK Guantanamo Bay detainee arrives in UK|work=[[BBC News]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=30 October 2015 |accessdate=30 October 2015}}</ref>\n*31 October \u2013 a motorist dies and ten people are taken to hospital with injuries, after a car collides with a bus near [[West Kilbride]] in [[Ayrshire]], Scotland.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-glasgow-west-34687469|title=Driver dies and two seriously injured in crash between car and bus|publisher=[[BBC]] |date=31 October 2015 |accessdate=31 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n===November===\n*1 November \u2013 a temperature of 22.4&nbsp;\u00b0C is recorded in [[Trawsgoed]], [[Ceredigion]] in [[Wales]], making it the warmest November day on record in the UK, breaking the previous record set nearly seventy years ago.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34693529|title=Hottest UK November day recorded in mid Wales|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=1 November 2015|accessdate=1 November 2015}}</ref>\n*2 November\n**Archaeologists accidentally discover a well-preserved family burial vault in [[Gloucester Cathedral]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-gloucestershire-32914568|title=Burial vault discovered 'accidentally' at Gloucester Cathedral|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=2 November 2015|accessdate=2 November 2015}}</ref>\n**Hundreds of police officers from all over the UK turn out to pay their respects at the funeral of [[Merseyside Police]] officer David Phillips at [[Liverpool Cathedral]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-34681868|title=PC David Phillips funeral: Hundreds of police officers attend|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=2 November 2015|accessdate=2 November 2015}}</ref>\n*4 November \u2013 a suspension of flights between the UK and the [[Egypt]]ian holiday resort of [[Sharm el-Sheikh]] leaves many British holidaymakers stranded, following rumours that the [[Metrojet Flight 9268]] on 31 October, in which many Russian tourists died, was caused by a terrorist bomb.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/nov/05/russian-plane-crash-media-anger-britain-stopping-sharm-el-sheikh|title=Anger in Russian media at Britain stopping Sharm el-Sheikh flights|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|date=5 November 2015|accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref>\n*5 November \u2013 a protest march by masked anti-capitalists in central [[London]] on Bonfire Night leads to three [[Metropolitan Police]] officers being taken to hospital with injuries. Six police horses are also hurt.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34741434|title=Million Mask March: Three police officers hospitalised|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=6 November 2015|accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref>\n*6 November \u2013 flights between the UK and [[Sharm el-Sheikh]] resume, bringing the stranded British tourists home.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34743388|title=Russian plane crash: First flights return to UK after Sharm alert|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=6 November 2015|accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref>\n*10 November \u2013 [[Storm Abigail]] is the first storm to be officially named by the [[Met Office]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metoffice.gov.uk/news/releases/archive/2015/storm-Abigail|title=Met Office officially names Abigail as first storm|publisher=Met Office|accessdate=10 November 2015}}</ref> It leaves many travel services disrupted, schools closed, and 20,000 homes without power.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34806420|title=Storm Abigail sweeps through Scotland cutting power|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=14 November 2015|accessdate=14 November 2015}}</ref>\n*11 November \u2013 the stepbrother of murdered teenager [[Murder of Becky Watts|Becky Watts]], Nathan Matthews is found guilty of her murder and his girlfriend, Sauna Hoare, found guilty of Becky Watts' manslaughter.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-34790804|title=Pair guilty of Becky Watts killing|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>\n*14 November\n**One Briton is confirmed to be among the 129 people killed in a series of coordinated [[November 2015 Paris attacks|terrorist attacks in Paris]] the previous day, with fears of a \"handful\" more to be confirmed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34821001|title=Paris attacks: Briton confirmed among dead|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=14 November 2015|accessdate=15 November 2015}}</ref>\n**[[Gatwick]]'s North Terminal is evacuated as a precautionary measure, in light of the [[November 2015 Paris attacks|terrorist attacks in Paris]], after a man is arrested when a suspicious item is found at the airport.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-sussex-34821392|title=French man held as suspected firearm found at Gatwick Airport|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=14 November 2015|accessdate=14 November 2015}}</ref>\n**The [[Department for Transport]] announces that all [[Traffic enforcement camera|speed cameras]] in England currently painted grey will be repainted yellow by the end of October 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-34819171|title=Grey speed cameras to be turned yellow under new rules|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=14 November 2015|accessdate=14 November 2015}}</ref>\n**A family of four are killed after their six-seater light aircraft crashes near [[Churchinford]] in [[Somerset]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-34822189|title=Four people dead as plane crashes in Somerset|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=14 November 2015|accessdate=14 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-somerset-34825769|title=Somerset plane crash dead 'from the same family'|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=15 November 2015|accessdate=15 November 2015}}</ref>\n*16 November \u2013 the UK joins the rest of Europe in a [[Moment of silence|minutes silence]] in remembrance of the 129 lives lost, including one Briton, in the [[November 2015 Paris attacks|Paris terrorist attacks]] on 13 November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34831380|title=UK falls silent for the victims of the Paris attacks|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=16 November 2015|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref>\n*17 November \u2013 Prime Minister David Cameron promises the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]] a \"comprehensive strategy\" to win MPs' backing for bombing [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]] militants in [[Syria]] as well as [[Iraq]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34846457|title=PM: I will make case for strikes against IS in Syria|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=17 November 2015|accessdate=17 November 2015}}</ref>\n*18 November\n**Thousands of homes are left without power as [[Storm Barney]] rips through parts of Britain.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/weather/12002488/Thousands-left-without-power-as-Storm-Barney-batters-UK.html|title=Thousands left without power as Storm Barney batters UK|publisher=The Telegraph|date=18 November 2015|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref>\n**Energy Secretary [[Amber Rudd]] proposes that the UK's [[Coal mining in the United Kingdom|coal plants]] should be phased out by 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34851718|title=UK's coal plants to be phased out within 10 years|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=18 November 2015|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref>\n*21 November \u2013 four Britons are believed to be among the seven people killed in a helicopter crash on the [[Fox Glacier]] in [[South Island]], New Zealand.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-34887978|title='Four Britons and two Australians' among NZ crash dead|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=21 November 2015|accessdate=21 November 2015}}</ref>\n*23 November \u2013 [[David Cameron]] holds talks with French President [[Francois Hollande]] about co-operation in the fight against [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34897288|title=David Cameron: World uniting to fight 'evil threat' of IS|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=23 November 2015|accessdate=23 November 2015}}</ref>\n*24 November\n**A [[Scottish National Party]] motion opposing [[Trident (missile)|Trident]]'s renewal is defeated by 330 votes to 64, with most Labour MPs abstaining.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34911204 MPs reject SNP calls for Trident to be scrapped] bbc.co.uk, accessed 26 December 2015</ref>\n**[[Alton Towers]] confirms that [[The Smiler (roller coaster)#Incidents|The Smiler rollercoaster crash]], that seriously injured five people in June, was caused by human error.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-34911943|title=Alton Towers Smiler ride crash due to 'human error'|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=24 November 2015|accessdate=24 November 2015}}</ref>\n**[[British Airways]] and [[EasyJet]] cancel all flights between [[Sharm el-Sheikh]] and the UK until January, following the suspected bombing of [[Metrojet Flight 9268]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34908420|title=Egypt plane crash: Airlines cancel more Sharm el-Sheikh flights|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=24 November 2015|accessdate=24 November 2015}}</ref>\n*25 November \u2013 Chancellor [[George Osborne]] outlines his joint annual [[Autumn Statement]] and [[Spending Review]] for the financial year ahead, in which he surprisingly announces he is to scrap planned cuts to [[tax credits]] and vows to protect police budgets in response to the UK's heightened terror threat.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34915218|title=Spending Review: George Osborne U-turn over tax credits|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=25 November 2015|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34922126|title=Spending Review: George Osborne protects police funding|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=25 November 2015|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref>\n*28 November \u2013 [[Grant Shapps]] quits as [[Minister of State]] at the [[Department for International Development]] amid claims he failed to act on allegations of bullying following the apparent suicide of a youth activist in September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34952981|title=Grant Shapps quits amid Tory bullying claims|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=28 November 2015|accessdate=28 November 2015}}</ref>\n*29 November \u2013 in tennis, Great Britain win the [[Davis Cup]] for the first time since [[1936 International Lawn Tennis Challenge|1936]] after [[Andy Murray]] beats Belgium's [[David Goffin]] at the final in [[Ghent]], Belgium.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/tennis/34957711|title=Andy Murray wins the Davis Cup for Great Britain|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=29 November 2015|accessdate=29 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n===December===\n*1 December \u2013 a fire damages a bar in [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]] city centre, and one person, later confirmed as the owner, Brian Sandals, is found burnt to death.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-tyne-34981621|title=Newcastle Kard Bar fire: Body believed to be Brian Sandals|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=2 December 2015|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref>\n*2 December \u2013 MPs vote 397>223 to authorise UK [[air strikes]] against [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]] in [[Syria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34989302|title=Syria air strikes: MPs authorise UK action against Islamic State|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=2 December 2015|accessdate=2 December 2015}}</ref>\n*3 December\n**The UK launches its first air strikes over Syria with [[RAF]] [[Panavia Tornado|tornado jets]] carrying out bombings against Islamic State-controlled oil fields.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34992032|title=UK launches first Syria air strikes|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=3 December 2015|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref>\n**The [[2015 Oldham West and Royton by-election|Oldham West and Royton by-election]], caused by long-serving MP [[Michael Meacher]]'s death in October, is held; Labour retains the seat with an increased majority of 7.3%.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-35003152|title=Jeremy Corbyn hails Oldham West and Royton by-election victory|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=4 December 2015|accessdate=4 December 2015}}</ref>\n*4 December\n**The Rail Delivery Group announces that rail fares will rise by 1.1% in the new year, in line with current inflation rates.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-35003820|title=Rail fares to rise by average of 1.1% from 2 January|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=4 December 2015|accessdate=5 December 2015}}</ref>\n**The [[Forth Road Bridge]] in Scotland is closed due to structural defects, and the Scottish Transport Minister, [[Derek Mackay]], declares that it will not be reopened until January 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-35001277|title=Forth Road Bridge to be closed until new year|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=4 December 2015|accessdate=5 December 2015}}</ref>\n*5 December\n**[[December 2015 London Underground attack|A stabbing at Leytonstone tube station]] in [[East London]], which leaves a man with serious knife injuries, is being treated as a \"terrorist incident\" according to the [[Metropolitan Police]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-35018789|title=Leytonstone Tube stabbing 'terrorist incident'|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=5 December 2015|accessdate=5 December 2015}}</ref>\n**[[Storm Desmond]] batters the UK with high-speed winds and heavy rain, causing severe disruption. People are evacuated from their homes as [[flash flooding]] sweeps through parts of [[Cumbria]], with police declaring a \"major incident\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-35014745|title=Storm Desmond brings flooding and disruption to parts of UK|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=5 December 2015|accessdate=5 December 2015}}</ref>\n**[[Plastic bag]] use in [[Tesco]] stores in England has declined by 80% since a new 5p charge was introduced, data suggests.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-35013520|title=Tesco plastic bag use 'down 80%' since 5p charge|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=5 December 2015|accessdate=5 December 2015}}</ref>\n*9 December\n**Election Court decide that although [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrat]] [[Alistair Carmichael]] had told a \"blatant lie\" in a TV interview, it had not been proven beyond reasonable doubt that he had committed an \"illegal practice\" that would invalidate his election.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-35049150|title=Alistair Carmichael case: Legal bid to oust Lib Dem MP fails|date=9 December 2015|work=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=9 December 2015}}</ref>\n**MPs debate whether [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] presidential candidate [[Donald Trump]] should be banned from entering the UK after an online petition receives an excess of 100,000 signatures. This followed Trump making a statement about banning all [[Muslims]] from entering the United States, and claims he made that parts of [[London]] are \"so radicalised the police are afraid for their lives\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-35052505|title=Trump UK ban petition passes 250,000 signatures|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=9 December 2015|accessdate=9 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-35037007|title=Trump claim wrong that police 'afraid' in London \u2013 PM says|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=9 December 2015|accessdate=9 December 2015}}</ref> \n**Chancellor [[George Osborne]] announces a \u00a350,000,000 fund for families and businesses hit by floods in Cumbria and [[Lancashire]] in the wake of Storm Desmond.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-35052705|title=Storm Desmond: \u00a350m flood fund pledged for victims|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=9 December 2015|accessdate=9 December 2015}}</ref>\n*10 December \u2013 the UK government announces that any decisions on whether to allow a new runway at [[London Heathrow Airport|Heathrow]] or [[Gatwick Airport|Gatwick]] will not be announced until the summer of 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-35062739|title=Heathrow Airport runway decision delayed until summer|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=10 December 2015|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref>\n*14 December \u2013 a \"huge rise\" is reported in the number of newborn babies in England who are subject to care proceedings, with 2,018 in 2013 compared to 802 in 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-35088794|title='Huge rise' in newborn babies subject to care proceedings|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=14 December 2015|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref>\n*15 December \u2013 British astronaut [[Tim Peake]] becomes the first Briton under the banner of the [[European Space Agency]] to set foot on the [[International Space Station]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-35101643|title=Tim Peake begins stay on international space station|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=15 December 2015|accessdate=12 January 2016}}</ref>\n*18 December\n**Britain's last deep [[coal mine]], [[Kellingley Colliery]] at [[Beal, North Yorkshire]], closes; marking the end of the era of deep-pit coal mining in Britain.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/news/regional/sadness-tinged-with-relief-for-miners-as-kellingley-colliery-closure-date-set-1-7619677|title=Sadness tinged with relief for miners as Kellingley Colliery closure date set|work=[[Yorkshire Evening Post]]|date=11 December 2015|accessdate=18 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222141314/http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/news/regional/sadness-tinged-with-relief-for-miners-as-kellingley-colliery-closure-date-set-1-7619677|archive-date=22 December 2015|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n**Energy firm [[RWE npower|npower]] is fined \u00a326,000,000 over billing and complaint failures after it sent out incorrect bills and failed to deal with complaints, according to [[Ofgem]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-35129788|title=Npower to pay \u00a326m over billing and complaint failures|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=18 December 2015|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref>\n*25 December \u2013 [[Storm Eva]] causes more intensive flooding in northern England, with homes evacuated in [[Lancashire]] and [[Yorkshire]], and rivers overflowing in [[Manchester]] and [[Leeds]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-35181139|title=UK floods: Homes evacuated amid heavy rain|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=27 December 2015|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref>\n*29 December \u2013 an 81-year-old woman is shot dead by a fellow octogenarian resident at the De La Mer House care home in [[Essex]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-35189664|title=De La Mer House care home shooting: Woman killed|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=29 December 2015|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref>\n*30 December\n**A husband and wife who plotted terror attacks in the [[London Underground|Underground]] and [[Westfield London|Westfield shopping centre]], nicknamed the \"silent bomber\" couple, are jailed for a minimum of 27 and 25 years.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-35198500|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=30 December 2015|accessdate=30 December 2015|title='Silent bomber' couple jailed for London terror plot}}</ref>\n**Hundreds of homes are evacuated and thousands are left without power in Scotland and Northern Ireland as [[Storm Frank]] brings torrential rain and gales. More than a hundred flood warnings are issued across England, Wales and Scotland.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-35181139|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=30 December 2015|accessdate=30 December 2015|title=UK floods: Homes evacuated amid heavy rain}}</ref>\n*31 December\n** The New Years honours list is announced, with new knights, dames, MBEs and OBEs awarded for notable contributions to society.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/dec/30/new-years-honours-2016-the-full-list|title=New Year honours 2016: the full list|date=30 December 2015|publisher=The Guardian}}</ref>\n** More than 1,700 same-sex couples married in the first year, after Scotland became the seventeenth country in the world to legalise same-sex marriage.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-35204654|title=More that 1,700 same-sex couples married in first year of law|date=31 December 2015|work=BBC News|accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n*[[Frances Hardinge]]'s young adult fantasy novel ''[[The Lie Tree]]'', overall winner of the [[2015 Costa Book Awards]].\n*[[Paula Hawkins (author)|Paula Hawkins]]' novel ''[[The Girl on the Train (novel)|The Girl on the Train]]''.\n*[[E. L. James]]' novel ''[[Grey: Fifty Shades of Grey as Told by Christian]]''.\n*[[Terry Pratchett]]'s posthumous novel ''[[The Shepherd's Crown]]''.\n*[[Jamie Oliver]]'s cookbook ''Everyday Super Food''.\n*[[Zoe Sugg]]'s novel ''[[Girl Online: On Tour]]''.\n*[[David Walliams]]' children's novel ''Grandpa's Great Escape''.\n\n==Births==\n\n===May===\n*2 May \u2013 [[Princess Charlotte of Cambridge]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-32562117|title=Royal baby Duchess of Cambridge gives birth to daughter|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=2 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Deaths==\n{{main|Deaths in 2015}}\n\n===January===\n[[File:Lord Brittan 2011.jpg|right|thumb|180px|[[Leon Brittan]] (1939\u20132015) in 2011]]\n[[File:8409Barrie.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Barrie Ingham]] (1932\u20132015) in 2011]]\n* 1 January\n**[[Barbara Atkinson]], 88, actress.\n**[[Matthew Cogley]], 30, musician and songwriter ([[Failsafe (UK band)|Failsafe]]).\n**[[Fiona Cumming]], 77, actress and director (''[[Doctor Who]]'').\n* 2 January\n**[[Danny Dunton]], 90, [[motorcycle speedway|speedway]] rider and promoter.\n**[[Bob Gilmore]], 53, musicologist.\n**[[Roger Kitter]], 64, actor (''[['Allo 'Allo!]]'')\n**[[Derek Minter]], 82, Grand Prix motorcycle and short-circuit road racer.<ref>{{cite web|last =Patterson|first=Simon|title =Derek Minter passes away aged 82|work =MCN|publisher =motorcyclenews.com|date =5 January 2015|url=http://www.motorcyclenews.com/sport/motogp/2015/january/derek-minter-passes-away-age-82/|accessdate =9 January 2015}}</ref>\n* 3 January \u2013 [[Terence Ranger]], 85, historian of Africa.\n* 4 January\n**[[John McPhee (footballer)|John McPhee]], 77, footballer ([[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]], [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]).\n**[[Bernard Williams (producer)|Bernard Williams]], 72, film producer (''[[A Clockwork Orange (film)|A Clockwork Orange]]'', ''[[Ragtime (film)|Ragtime]]'', ''[[Star Trek Generations]]'').\n* 5 January\n**[[Khan Bonfils]], 42, a