sh television]]\n* [[2015 in England]]\n* [[2015 in Northern Ireland]]\n* [[2015 in Scotland]]\n* [[2015 in Wales]]\n* [[List of British films of 2015]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Years in the United Kingdom}}\n{{Year in Europe|2015}}\n\n[[Category:2015 in the United Kingdom| ]]\n[[Category:Years of the 21st century in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2015 by country|United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2014}}\n{{Year in United Kingdom|2015\n|label1= Individual countries of the United Kingdom\n|data1 = [[2015 in England|England]] {{!}} [[2015 in Northern Ireland|Northern Ireland]] {{!}} [[2015 in Scotland|Scotland]] {{!}} [[2015 in Wales|Wales]]\n|label2= Sport, television and music\n|data2 = <div>\n[[Football in the United Kingdom|Football]]: [[2014\u201315 in English football|England]] {{!}} [[2014\u201315 in Scottish football|Scotland]] {{!}} [[2014\u201315 in Welsh football|Wales]]<br />\n[[2015 British Grand Prix]]<br />\n[[2015 English cricket season]]<br />\n[[2015 in British television]]<br />\n[[2015 in British music]]<br />\n[[2015 in British radio]]<br />\n[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2015|UK in the Eurovision Song Contest 2015]]\n</div>\n}}\nEvents from the year '''[[2015]] in the [[United Kingdom]]'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n*[[Monarch of the United Kingdom|Monarch]] \u2013 [[Elizabeth II]]\n*[[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]] \u2013 [[David Cameron]] ([[Cameron\u2013Clegg coalition|Coalition]] until 8 May, [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] starting 8 May)\n*[[Parliament of the United Kingdom|Parliament]]\n** [[List of MPs elected in the 2010 United Kingdom general election|55th]] (until 30 March)\n** [[List of MPs elected in the 2015 United Kingdom general election|56th]] (starting 27 May)\n\n==Events==\n\n===January===\n*2 January \u2013 [[Buckingham Palace]] denies \"any suggestion of impropriety with underage minors\" by [[Prince Andrew, Duke of York]], after he was named in U.S. court documents related to a lawsuit against convicted sex offender, American financier [[Jeffrey Epstein]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-30659629 |title=Prince Andrew sex case claim denied |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=2 January 2015 |accessdate=2 January 2015}}</ref>\n*3 January \u2013 eight people are reported missing after a cargo vessel, the ''[[List of shipwrecks in 2015|Cemfjord]]'', capsizes in the [[Pentland Firth]], Scotland.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-highlands-islands-30667084 |title=Major search after ship overturns off north of Scotland |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=3 January 2015 |accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-north-east-orkney-shetland-30670842 |title=Cemfjord survivor chances said to be 'very slim' |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=4 January 2015 |accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref>\n*4 January \u2013 the ''[[MV H\u00f6egh Osaka|H\u00f6egh Osaka]]'', a Singaporean cargo ship transporting luxury cars, runs aground near the [[Isle of Wight]] after it started listing shortly after leaving the [[Port of Southampton]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-hampshire-30670746 |title=Crew rescued from listing Solent car transporter |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=4 January 2015 |accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref> An investigation is launched.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-hampshire-30677320 |title=Cargo ship Solent: Salvage team boards stranded vessel |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=5 January 2015 |accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref>\n*6 January \n**Figures from the last three months show that England's hospital [[Accident & Emergency]] waiting time performance has dropped to its worst levels for a decade.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-30692497 |title=A&E waiting in England worst for a decade |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=6 January 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2015}}</ref>\n**Comedian and actor [[Stephen Fry]] confirms he is to [[Same-sex marriage in the United Kingdom|marry his partner]], Elliott Spencer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-norfolk-30693048 |title=Stephen Fry to marry partner Elliott Spencer |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=6 January 2015 |accessdate=6 January 2015}}</ref> The couple are married two weeks later at a registry office in Norfolk.<ref>{{cite news|first=Nadia |last=Khomami |url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2015/jan/17/stephen-fry-elliott-spencer-marries-twitter |title=Stephen Fry marries partner Elliot Spencer |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=17 January 2015 |accessdate=13 February 2015}}</ref>\n*7 January \u2013 the [[Society of Motor Manufacturers and Traders|SMMT]] announce that car sales surged in 2014 with 2.47 million new cars registered; a 9% increase from 2013 and the best annual performance since 2004.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-30706580 |title=UK new car sales surge to 10-year high in 2014 |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=7 January 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2015}}</ref>\n*9 January\n**Hurricane-force winds cause travel disruption and leave tens of thousands of homes without power across Scotland.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-highlands-islands-30726678 |title=Hurricane-force gusts cause disruption to power and travel |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=9 January 2015 |accessdate=9 January 2015}}</ref>\n**[[Circle (healthcare partnership)|Circle Holdings]], the first private company to operate an [[NHS England|NHS]] hospital, announces plans to withdraw from its contract to run [[Hinchingbrooke Hospital]] because it believes the franchise is \"no longer viable under current terms\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-cambridgeshire-30740956 |title=Hinchingbrooke Hospital: Circle to withdraw from contract |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=9 January 2015 |accessdate=9 January 2015}}</ref>\n**Chancellor [[George Osborne]] says that tackling [[terrorism]] is a \"national priority\" and security services will get all of the resources they need in light of the recent [[Charlie Hebdo shooting|''Charlie Hebdo'' attacks]] in [[Paris]], and the [[MI5]] confirming that three UK plots had been recently stopped.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-30740614 |title=Osborne: Tackling UK terror threat a \"national priority\" |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=9 January 2015 |accessdate=9 January 2015}}</ref>\n**[[Abu Hamza al-Masri|Abu Hamza]], the former head of London's [[Finsbury Park mosque]] who preached [[Islamic terrorism]], is sentenced to life in prison by a US court.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-30754959 |title=Radical cleric Abu Hamza jailed for life by US court |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=9 January 2015 |accessdate=9 January 2015}}</ref>\n*11 January \u2013 major [[London]] landmarks, including [[Trafalgar Square]] and [[Tower Bridge]], are lit in the colours of the [[Flag of France|French national flag]] in tribute to the victims of the recent [[January 2015 \u00cele-de-France attacks|terrorist attacks]] in [[Paris]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-30766218 |title=Paris attacks: London landmarks lit in French colours |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=11 January 2015 |accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>\n*12 January\n**19-year-old Lewis Daynes who murdered 14-year-old [[Murder of Breck Bednar|Breck Bednar]] after meeting him online in February 2014, is sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-30786021 |title=Breck Bednar murder: Lewis Daynes sentenced to life in prison |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=12 January 2015 |accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref>\n**Security chiefs meet with [[David Cameron]] to review the risk of a terrorist attack, similar to the recent [[January 2015 \u00cele-de-France attacks|attacks]] in [[Paris]], as the likelihood of such an event becomes greater.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-30772035 |title=Cameron discusses risk of Paris-style attack in UK |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=12 January 2015 |accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref>\n**[[David Cameron]] brands [[Fox News Channel|Fox News]]' terror expert a \"complete idiot\" after he claims that [[Birmingham]] is \"totally Muslim\" and \"non-Muslims just simply don't go in\".{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n*13 January \u2013 figures show that [[inflation]] rates fell to 0.5% in December, the joint lowest on record, mainly due to the drop in fuel prices.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-30794673 |title=UK inflation rate falls to 0.5% in December |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=13 January 2015 |accessdate=13 January 2015}}</ref>\n*14 January\n**The [[Met Office]] warns that a storm, dubbed \"Storm Rachel\", will bring snow, ice, rain, floods and gale-force winds to the UK.<ref>{{cite news|first=Turner |last=Camilla |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/weather/11341325/Everything-you-need-to-know-about-Storm-Rachel.html |title=Everything you need to know about 'Storm Rachel' |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=14 January 2015}}</ref> This is after severe heavy snow and gales hit Scotland, and a tornado struck homes in [[Wales]] the previous night.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-30804065 |title=Snow and gales bring disruption to UK |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=14 January 2015}}</ref>\n**[[Ed Miliband]], [[Nick Clegg]] and [[Nigel Farage]], the leaders respectively of [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]], the [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] and the [[UK Independence Party]], have written to Prime Minister and [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]] leader [[David Cameron]] to say that they will still take part in the planned pre-election televised debates even if he is not present. Cameron had said he would not take part unless the [[Green Party of England and Wales|Green Party]] was included, but the other leaders will call for the various broadcasters holding the debates to include an empty podium, enabling Cameron to be included if he changes his mind.<ref>{{cite news|first=Rowena |last=Mason |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/jan/14/pressure-on-cameron-over-tv-debates |title=David Cameron under growing pressure over TV debates |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=14 January 2015}}</ref>\n*15 January\n**A set of council offices, a funeral parlour, and a thatched cottage are extensively damaged after they are set ablaze due to a spate of [[arson]] attacks in [[South Oxfordshire]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-oxfordshire-30826330 |title=Arson attack guts Oxfordshire District Council building |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=15 January 2015 |accessdate=15 January 2015}}</ref> A suspect is arrested.<ref>{{cite news|first=Weaver |last=Matthew |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jan/15/oxfordshire-fires-believed-work-arsonists-district-council |title=Suspected arsonist held over Oxfordshire fires |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=15 January 2015 |accessdate=15 January 2015}}</ref>\n** [[Ethel Lang (supercentenarian)|Ethel Lang]], the last person living in the UK who was born during the reign of [[Queen Victoria]], dies at the age of 114.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-south-yorkshire-30845570 |title=Britain's oldest person Ethel Lang dies aged 114 |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=16 January 2015 |accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref>\n*16 January \u2013 UK counter-terrorism police warn that members of the Jewish community could be at risk following the recent [[January 2015 \u00cele-de-France attacks|terror incidents]] in Paris.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-30854519 |work=[[BBC News]] |title=Paris attacks: UK police 'concerned' for Jewish community |publisher=[[BBC]]|date=16 January 2015|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref>\n*21 January\n**Sir [[John Chilcot]] says that [[Chilcot report|his report]] into the [[2003 invasion of Iraq|Iraq war]] will be published after the general election. A draft version has been completed, but time is needed for those criticised by the findings of the inquiry to respond.<ref>{{cite news|first=Patrick |last=Wintour |first2=Frances |last2=Perraudin |first3=Nicholas |last3=Watt |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jan/21/chilcott-summoned-parliament-iraq-war-report-delays |title=Chilcot confirms delay to publication of Iraq war report |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=21 January 2015 |accessdate=21 January 2015}}</ref>\n**''[[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]'' defiantly denies that it is to cease publishing topless women on [[Page 3]] after posting a preview of its next publication featuring topless model Nicole Neal, calling the recent absence of the feature a \"[[Mammary gland|mammary]] lapse\".<ref>{{cite news|first=Justin |last=Harp |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/media/news/a623363/the-sun-defiantly-denies-banning-page-3-topless-photos.html#~p23aFtj1pA3jsG |title=The Sun defiantly denies banning Page 3 topless photos |publisher=Hearst Magazines UK |newspaper=Digital Spy |date=21 January 2015 |accessdate=22 January 2015}}</ref>\n*23 January \u2013 new proposals are published by the UK's major broadcasters to include the leaders of more political parties in the forthcoming televised debates. The [[BBC]] and [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] will now host seven-way debates between the leaders of the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]], [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]], the [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]], [[UK Independence Party]], the [[Green Party (UK)|Green Party]], the [[Scottish National Party]] and [[Plaid Cymru]]. Meanwhile, [[Channel 4]] and [[Sky (UK & Ireland)|Sky]] will host head-to-head debates between [[David Cameron]] and [[Ed Miliband]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-30955379 |title=Election 2015: Seven-party TV debate plan announced |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=23 January 2015 |accessdate=23 January 2015}}</ref>\n*24 January\n**[[David Cameron]] and [[HRH Prince Charles]] fly to [[Saudi Arabia]] to pay respects to the late [[Abdullah of Saudi Arabia|King Abdullah]] who died the previous day.<ref>{{cite news|first=Andrew |last=Sparrow |first2=Frances |last2=Perraudin |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jan/24/prince-charles-and-pm-fly-to-saudi-amid-growing-row-over-uk-flag-tributes |title=Prince Charles and PM fly to Saudi amid growing row over UK flag tributes |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=24 January 2015 |accessdate=24 January 2015}}</ref>\n**[[UKIP|UK Independence Party]] MEP [[Amjad Bashir]] defects to the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]], describing his former party as one of \"ruthless self-interest\". In response, UKIP claims Bashir was suspended from the party over \"extremely serious\" financial issues, something the MEP dismisses as \"absurd and made-up allegations\".<ref>{{cite news|first=Lin |last=Jenkins |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/jan/24/ukip-amjad-bashir-defects-conservatives |title=UKIP MEP Amjad Bashir defects to the Conservatives |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=24 January 2015 |accessdate=24 January 2015}}</ref>\n*26 January \u2013 [[Libby Lane]] becomes the first woman ordained as a bishop in the [[Church of England]], at [[York Minster]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-30974547 |title=Libby Lane: First female Church of England bishop consecrated |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=26 January 2015 |accessdate=26 January 2015}}</ref>\n*27 January \u2013 [[Helen Macdonald (author)|Helen Macdonald]] wins the [[2014 Costa Book Awards]] with her autobiography ''[[H is for Hawk]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31009421 |title=Helen Macdonald wins Costa Book of the Year 2014 |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=27 January 2015 |accessdate=27 January 2015}}</ref>\n*28 January \u2013 an [[List of earthquakes in the British Isles#21st century|earthquake]] of magnitude 3.8 is felt across the [[East Midlands]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-31032930 |title=East Midlands tremor recorded at 3.8 in magnitude |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=29 January 2015 |accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n*30 January \u2013 commemorations are made for the fiftieth anniversary of [[Sir Winston Churchill]]'s [[Later life of Winston Churchill#funeral|funeral]], including a church service at [[Westminster Abbey]], and the retracing of the same boat journey that carried Churchill's coffin along the [[River Thames]] in 1965.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-31041370 |title=Sir Winston Churchill's funeral marked 50 years on |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=30 January 2015 |accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n*31 January \u2013 the head of the [[Police Federation of England and Wales]] expresses his controversial support for all front-line police officers in England and Wales to be offered [[Tasers]] in light of the increased terrorism threat to the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-31071922 |title='Tasers for all front-line officers' \u2013 Police Federation |publisher=BBC |work=BBC News |date=31 January 2015 |accessdate=31 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===February===\n*2 February \u2013 [[London]]'s population hits a record high of 8,600,000 which it hasn't seen since the beginning of the Second World War in 1939, and is forecast to reach 11,000,000 people by 2050.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-31082941 |title=London's population hits 8.6m record high |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=2 February 2015 |accessdate=2 February 2015}}</ref>\n*3 February \u2013 MPs approve a controversial new technique to allow [[Three-parent baby|babies created from three people]]. If passed by the [[House of Lords]], the UK will become the first country in the world to offer this medical procedure.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-31069173 |title=MPs say yes to three-person babies |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=3 February 2015 |accessdate=3 February 2015}}</ref>\n*4 February\n**The entire cabinet of [[Rotherham Metropolitan Borough Council|Rotherham Borough Council]] announces its intention to resign from office, following a report into the [[Rotherham child sexual exploitation scandal]] concludes the council's handling of the scandal was \"not fit for purpose\".<ref>{{cite news|first=Helen |last=Pidd |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/feb/04/rotherham-council-denial-child-sexual-exploitation-failures-report |title=Rotherham council cabinet to resign after damning child exploitation report |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=4 February 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n**[[Home Secretary]] [[Theresa May]] appoints New Zealand judge [[Lowell Goddard]] to lead a new [[Independent Panel Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse|statutory inquiry into historical child sexual abuse]].<ref>{{cite news|first=David |last=Barrett |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/11388962/New-Zealand-judge-set-to-chair-child-abuse-inquiry.html |title=New Zealand judge Lowell Goddard to chair child abuse inquiry |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=4 February 2015 |accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n*5 February \u2013 former pop star [[Gary Glitter]] is found guilty of sexually abusing three young girls between 1975\u20131980.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-31153633 |title=Gary Glitter trial: Singer guilty of historical sex abuse |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=5 February 2015 |accessdate=5 February 2015}}</ref>\n*6 February\n**Huge changes to England's [[National Health Service (England)|NHS]] in recent years have been \"disastrous\" and distracted from patient care, a report by the King's Fund says.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-31145600 |title=NHS reorganisation was disastrous, says King's Fund |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=6 February 2015 |accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n**The Investigatory Powers Tribunal rules that [[GCHQ]] breached human rights laws by failing to disclose shared full details of information it shared with the United States that was garnered from data from mass internet surveillance.<ref>{{cite news|first=Owen |last=Bowcott |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/feb/06/gchq-mass-internet-surveillance-unlawful-court-nsa |title=UK-US surveillance regime was unlawful \u2018for seven years\u2019 |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=6 February 2015 |accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref>\n*9 February \u2013 a child and three adults are killed whilst four others are left seriously injured after a [[tipper truck]] crashes down a hill in [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-bristol-31321186 |title=Bath tipper truck crash kills child and three adults |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=9 February 2015 |accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref> An investigation is launched.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-bristol-31339654 |title=Bath fatal tipper truck crash investigated |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=10 February 2015 |accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref>\n*11 February \u2013 the government announces a review into road regulations and maintenance checks in preparation for [[Autonomous car|driverless car]] technology.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-31364441 |title=Driverless car review launched by UK government |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=11 February 2015 |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n*13 February\n**Former TV weather presenter [[Fred Talbot]] is convicted of indecently assaulting two boys while he worked at a school in Greater Manchester, and remanded in custody to await sentence. He is cleared of a further eight charges.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-31456840 |title=Fred Talbot: Weatherman guilty of abusing teenage boys |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=13 February 2015 |accessdate=13 February 2015}}</ref>\n**The [[David Cameron|Prime Minister]], [[Nick Clegg|Deputy Prime Minister]] and [[Ed Miliband|Leader of the Opposition]] sign a cross-party, non-partisan agreement to tackle [[Climate change in the United Kingdom|climate change]], seek a strong [[2015 United Nations Climate Change Conference|global climate deal]], and to end the use of [[Coal mining in the United Kingdom|coal]] for power generation in the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://m.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-31456161 |title=Party leaders make joint climate commitment |work=BBC |date=14 February 2015 |accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.green-alliance.org.uk/leaders_joint_climate_change_agreement.php |title=Cameron, Clegg and Miliband sign joint climate change agreement |work=Green Alliance |date=14 February 2015 |accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n*14 February \u2013 four people are killed following two separate accidents on major motorways; three die after a coach collides with a stationary car on the [[M1 motorway|M1]] and one person dies in a forty vehicle pileup on the [[M40 motorway|M40]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1427453/four-die-in-coach-crash-and-motorway-pile-up |title=Four Die In Coach Crash And Motorway Pile-Up |publisher=British Sky Broadcasting |work=Sky News |date=14 February 2015 |accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n*16 February \u2013 a study by [[King's College London]] indicates an increased risk of [[psychosis]] among those who smoke potent [[cannabis]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-31480234 |title='Skunk-like cannabis' increases risk of psychosis, study suggests |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=16 February 2015 |accessdate=16 February 2015}}</ref>\n*17 February\n**Consumer price inflation fell to 0.3% in January, according to latest official figures, its lowest level since records began.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-31501805 |title=UK inflation rate falls to record low of 0.3% in January |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=17 February 2015 |accessdate=18 February 2015}}</ref>\n**Abid Naseer, a man who plotted a terrorist attack on a [[Manchester Arndale|shopping centre]] in [[Manchester]] in 2009, which would have reportedly only come second to the [[September 11 terrorist attacks|September 11 attacks]] in its impact, stands on trial in the United States.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2015-02-17/man-who-plotted-manchester-terror-attack-goes-on-trial-in-us/ |title=Man 'who plotted Manchester terror attack' goes on trial in US |publisher=ITV |work=ITV News |date=17 February 2015 |accessdate=17 February 2015}}</ref>\n**Five Britons are amongst the 100 [[Mars One]] applicants shortlisted for a one-way trip to [[Mars]] to become the first humans to set foot on the planet.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/space/11416615/Mars-One-mission-5-Britons-shortlisted-for-one-way-trip-to-Red-Planet.html |title=Mars One mission: five Britons shortlisted for one-way trip to Red Planet |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=17 February 2015 |accessdate=17 February 2015}}</ref>\n*18 February \u2013 the [[Metropolitan Police Service|Metropolitan Police]] says it will examine video footage appearing to show fans of [[Chelsea F.C|Chelsea football club]] preventing a black man from boarding a train on the [[Paris Metro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-31520745 |title=Chelsea fans Paris footage examined by UK police |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=18 February 2015 |accessdate=18 February 2015}}</ref>\n*20 February \u2013 police appeal for help after it is feared that three [[London]] schoolgirls who have gone missing, are travelling to [[Turkey]] with the intention of crossing the border into [[Syria]] and joining a terror group [[ISIL]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/11424884/Three-missing-British-schoolgirls-travel-to-Syria.html |title=Three missing London schoolgirls 'travelling to Syria to join Isil' |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=20 February 2015 |accessdate=21 February 2015}}</ref>\n*21 February \u2013 the government pledges \u00a3300,000,000 for tackling [[dementia]], aiming to become a \"world leader\" in research with a global fund to produce new treatments by 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-31557377 |title=Alzheimer's charity hails one million 'dementia friends' |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=[[BBC News]] |date=21 February 2015 |accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/health/elder/11426850/David-Cameron-announces-300m-for-dementia-research.html |title=David Cameron announces \u00a3300m for dementia research |publisher=[[BBC]] |work=The Telegraph |date=21 February 2015 |accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref>\n*24 February \u2013 Conservative MP Sir [[Malcolm Rifkind]] resigns as Chair of the Parliamentary Intelligence and S