ays during a visit to China that the country \"must be the United Kingdom's number two export market\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34325714|title='China must be our number two export market'|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=22 September 2015|accessdate=22 September 2015}}</ref>\n*26 September \u2013 a fire damages the United Kingdom's largest mosque, the [[Baitul Futuh Mosque]] in Morden, London.<ref>{{cite news|title=Morden mosque fire: 70 firefighters tackle blaze|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-34369710|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=26 September 2015|accessdate=26 September 2015}}</ref>\n*28 September \u2013 steelmaker [[Sahaviriya Steel Industries|SSI]], owner of the [[Teesside Steelworks]] at [[Redcar]] in North Yorkshire, announces that it is to close, with the loss of 1,700 jobs.<ref>{{cite news| title=SSI Redcar steel plant mothballed, with the loss of 1,700 jobs|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-34377756|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=28 September 2015|accessdate=29 September 2015}}</ref>\n*30 September\n**[[Volkswagen]] announces that 1,200,000 of its vehicles sold in the UK are affected by the software behind the [[Volkswagen emissions violations|emissions scandal]], including cars with the VW brand, Audi, Seat, Skod\u0103 and VW vans.<ref>{{cite news|title=VW scandal: 1.2m UK vehicles affected |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34399503|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=30 September 2015|accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref>\n**David Cameron faces demands from campaigners to apologise and pay financial reparations for [[Slavery in the British Isles|Britain's role]] in the historic [[slave trade]] in the [[Caribbean]], during a state visit to [[Jamaica]].<ref>{{cite news|title=David Cameron faces demands for slavery reparation on Jamaica visit|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-34401412|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=30 September 2015|accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref> Government loans taken out to compensate slaveowners under the [[Slaver